								<p>This recipe is a Middle Eastern take on a mac &#8216;n&#8217; cheese thanks to the addition of cumin, a herbaceous za&#8217;atar pesto and crispy fried onions. Cooking the macaroni in the milk, as we do here, bypasses having to make a béchamel. The starches are released into the soon-to-be-cheesy sauce, making it velvety and rich without the need for the more traditional flour-butter &#8216;roux&#8217;.</p>
<p>To make the crispy onions, finely slice a couple of onions into thin rounds, and toss with 2 tablespoons of cornflour, then fry in hot vegetable oil in about three batches, for 4 minutes per batch, or until golden.</p>
